The Independent Electoral Commission says the low number of youth participating in elections is a weakness in our democracy and needs to be addressed urgently. The IEC has launched a voter registration drive at tertiary institutions aimed at reversing this trend. eNCA's Govan Whittles has the details. #eNCA #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - The Independent Electoral Commission says the low number of youth participating in elections is a weakness in our democracy and needs to be addressed urgently. The IEC has launched a voter registration drive at tertiary institutions aimed at reversing this trend. Last year’s voter turnout during the local government elections was the worst on record since 1994. eNCA's Govan Whittles has the details in the video above. 